The service was great and friendly. They had a wide variety of food, however it was not that good. We ordered morocho and not only was watery, it tasted like water with sugar and vanilla- with a hint of coconut 🤷🏻‍♀️ The bandera - the guatita was so watery, but it was tasty/ the goat also watery but tasty. The ceviche needed salt - had no taste, I had to add the non spicy-hot sauce (delicious) for flavor. The hornado was delicious. We also had the arroz marinero which was just okay - it had imitation crab & tuna (WHY?!🤷🏻‍♀️🤷🏻‍♀️). I am Ecuadorian and know my food and people, and it seems that the folks that cook are from the Sierra which are not the best at making food from the coast. I recommend to have food from that region such as the Horando which was delicious. I wouldn't recommend to bring children either, it's more like a sports bar feel... they had a soccer game on and all the intoxicated guests were screaming like maniacs and cursing. They not only scared me, but the 3 year old we were with. We only stopped by because it had good reviews in Google. Needless to say, I will not be coming back.
